metadata.name: Fossil #35
metadata.description:
An impression of a fossilized creature is frozen in time in this generative artwork.  Features vectored ellipses and stochastic abstractions.

Created using p5js.

Press the Down Arrow to save the frame as a png.
Click or tap the canvas to toggle full screen.

metadata.name: Unicorn #2662
metadata.description:
All of us have dreams, and everyone would like to meet a fairy, a genie, a wizard, or someone else who will make our dreams come true in a snap of a finger or with the wave of a wand. But we're the only ones who can do it. We are those magical unicorns, unique, inimitable, with our own qualities and magical abilities.
These unicorns are the visualization of our inner selves that makes our dreams come true. An embodiment of all the best with a huge positive magical power.

Twitter: @unicorn_nft_art
Web: https://unicorn-nft.web.app/

by @lucky26puch, @AgataBaranova17

metadata.name: Swirl World #26
metadata.description: In this piece different generative geometric shapes fade off into the distance using a mathematical swirl pattern. At least in some of my favorite iterations. In life patterns occur and these patterns change and shift over time. The swirls in this animation are similar to those that occur in nature. For example a snails shell or flower.

metadata.name: Lakes and Mountains Ink Painting #28
metadata.description:
Ink wash painting is a type of Chinese ink brush painting which uses black ink, such as that used in Chinese calligraphy, in different concentrations.
In landscape painting the scenes depicted are typically imaginary, or very loose adaptations of actual views.
-
All made with p5js

metadata.name: White Poppy 30 #184
metadata.description: 30-degree variations of a White Poppy.. The flower was 3D scanned, producing a 15 millions vertices point cloud. The point cloud was then simplified to 350k vertices, in order to be used here. This piece can still be a bit resource intensive. You can click/tap (or press 's') to stop the spinning, this should help if your device is struggling - @smallfly

metadata.name: musical society #327
metadata.description:
society.png: musical society is a collaborative PFP work drawn by Tito Yusuf and directed by Sandy Pirouzi with the aim to facilitate Tezos newcomers with affordable PFP to rock.

This series is taking inspiration from a music scene that Tito is part of. Some traits are paying tribute to some of Tezos musicians such as Jburn, Musical Jackal, Binerica, and Sigmun.

---------------------------------------------
  Most will be us
Some are pretending to be us
Some others are even not us
(And few of them are not even alive anymore)
---------------------------------------------

  PS Tito is a master at bad drawing. Don’t expect fine lines with perfect alignment in his drawing (but the colors are fun!).

  PPS There’s no utility in this project except the CC0 license, so just have fun with it ;)  

Special thanks to:
 purespider for the template and assistance
Jburn, IndraAziz (Musical Jackal), Binerica, Mirffu (Sigmun) for allowing the making and usage of respective traits
ciphrd and fx(hash) team for allowing the making and usage of fx(hash) traits

 Type: Image Composition
 Dimension: 1000 x 1000 px
License for visual: CC0 
License for code: MIT

Twitter: @titoys90 @spirouzi

metadata.description:
Retro sci-fi style landscape sketch drawn by code.

Features:
- Terrain: Cliff, Cavern, Sky, Megalopolis, Desert, Sea, Space, Volcano
- Orientation: Landscape, Portlait
- Palette: White, Cream, Tan, Pink, Green, Yellow, Orange
- Background: Light, Dark

Live view options:

Depending on the device you run it on, it may take some time for the drawing to complete.
Made with p5js.

June 2022

metadata.name: One Tezo Drawings_286+ #1
metadata.description:
The One Tezo Drawings project is a variation of the “Desenhos de um Real” project (2006- ). In it, the artist sets the price of his work by making a rational calculation, equating his artistic production with a consumer good detached from the art world .
In this case, the calculation is based on the amount charged per hour of work from the minimum wage in the United States. Thus, a drawing that took X hours to produce (Wt) will have its price fixed at USD 15.00 * Wt divided by the value in Dollars of one Tezo (Dt) at the time of publication. But for the final price to be 1.00 Tez, the total production time value (Wt) will be divided by the number of editions (Ed). Therefore, the number of editions is defined by the following formula: 1.00 Tez = (Wt*15/Dt)/Ed ==> 

Ed=Wt*15/Dt 


For this particular project:
Permutation of 23 almost mirrored layers of “One Tezo Drawings” and ”One Tezo Drawings_65+”

Wt= 3.5
Dt= 2.22
Ed= 3.5*15/2.22 = 24

Press J or P to save a 1500x1500px image
